# WhenToBoat — Environment Variables
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in the values to run the app locally.
# Never commit .env.local — it is in .gitignore by default in Next.js projects.

# Mapbox public token used by the map view (client-side).
#
# How to get one:
#   1. Sign up at https://www.mapbox.com/
#   2. Create a token at https://account.mapbox.com/access-tokens/
#   3. Restrict the token to:
#      - Scopes: styles:read, fonts:read, datasets:read (defaults are fine)
#      - URLs: localhost:3000 + your production domain + Vercel preview domains
#        (e.g., localhost:3000, *.vercel.app, whentoboat.com)
#
# IMPORTANT: This token is exposed to the browser by design (NEXT_PUBLIC_*).
# URL restriction in the Mapbox dashboard is what protects it from abuse on
# other domains. Do NOT use a default unrestricted account token.
NEXT_PUBLIC_MAPBOX_TOKEN=pk.your_mapbox_public_token_here
